# Claude Code Docker Container Configuration

# Authentication: OAuth (for organization access via Claude Console)
# No configuration needed - Claude Code will use OAuth authentication
# The script automatically mounts your local Claude config directory to persist OAuth tokens
# You'll be prompted to authenticate via browser on first run

# OPTIONAL: Additional repositories to mount in the container
# Comma-separated list of absolute paths to git repositories
# Example: CLAUDE_REPOS=/home/user/project1,/home/user/project2
# These will be mounted as: /workspace/project1, /workspace/project2
# CLAUDE_REPOS=

# Note: The current directory is always mounted automatically at /workspace/current
